Immediate-past Rivers State Accountant-General, Siminialayi Fubara, polled 721 votes to defeat 15 other aspirants with Isaac Kamalu coming a distant second with 86 votes. Fubara hails from the riverine Opobo-Nkoro Local Government Area.   Ekweremadu withdraws as 11 step down for Mbah     Fintiri picks Adamawa ticket     Abaribe kicks as former ABSU VC is declared winner   While Felix Obua got two votes, David Brigs got four, West Morgan got four, Tammy Danagogo got 36 and George Kelly polled 37. A team from the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) monitored the process with Governor Nyesom Wike in attendance. Some major aspirants such as a former state Chairman of PDP, Felix Obua and former Secretary to State Government (SSG), Tammy Danagogo; Senator Thompson Sekibo, Austin Opara, Senator Lee Maeba were not in attendance.